9 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
10 SECTION 1. SHORT TITLE. This act shall be known and may be cited as the
11 "Investing in Mothers and Family Act."
12 SECTION 2. That Chapter 8, Title 57, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
13 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
14 ignated as Section 57-829, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
15 57-829. CHOOSE LIFE IDAHO FUND. (1) There is hereby created in the
16 state treasury the choose life Idaho fund. Moneys in the fund shall be appro-
17 priated to choose life Idaho, inc. for the purpose of:
18 (a) Assisting other organizations that are tax-exempt pursuant to sec-
19 tion 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code and that provide life-af-
20 firming counseling, care, and assistance for women and families to en-
21 courage alternatives to abortion; and
22 (b) Education of the public for support of adoption as a positive choice
23 for women and families who are at risk of choosing abortion.
24 (2) Moneys in the fund shall be appropriated for use in Idaho only.
25 SECTION 3. That Section 63-3029C, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
26 amended to read as follows:
27 63-3029C. INCOME TAX CREDIT FOR CERTAIN CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS --
28 LIMITATION. At the election of the taxpayer, there shall be allowed, subject
29 to the applicable limitations provided herein, as a credit against the in-
30 come tax imposed by chapter 30, title 63, Idaho Code, an amount equal to fifty
31 percent (50%) of the aggregate amount of charitable contributions made by
32 such taxpayer during the year to the anchor house or its foundation, to the
33 children's home society of Idaho, inc., to the Idaho youth ranch or its foun-
34 dation, to kinderhaven or its foundation, to the women's and children's al-
35 liance or its foundation, to children's village, inc. or its foundation, to
36 Idaho drug free youth, inc. or its foundation, to gem youth services or its
37 foundation, to the hope house, inc. or its foundation, to the north Idaho
38 children's home or its foundation, to the shepherd's home, inc. or its foun-
39 dation, to a project safe place located within the state of Idaho, to the
40 learning lab, inc. or its foundation, to a center for independent living lo-

